Reasoning: The paper deals with the characterization of the Generalized Degrees of Freedom (GDoF) of the two-user interference channel under finite precision channel state information at the transmitters (CSIT) and limited cooperation. This falls under the domain of Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networked Systems (cs.NI). The paper also involves the study of interference channels (cs.SI) and the use of Aligned Images bounds (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper deals with the concept of shared messages (cs.CC).
